description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting vacancy has arisen for a full time (37.5 hours per week) community respiratory physiotherapist to join the Community Respiratory Team, providing specialist care and advice to patients with chronic respiratory disease in Cambridgeshire. We would welcome applicants to apply for the post as a Band 5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base address is flexible and can be discussed at interview, this post will include significant amounts of travel. The ability to work flexibly across the county wide respiratory team is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post entails providing expert supportive care for respiratory patients. A large component of this post will be delivering Pulmonary Rehabilitation Courses to patients in the Huntingdon and Cambridge area under the supervision of a Band 6 Physiotherapist. &lt;br /&gt;Other roles, dependent upon experience of the successful candidate, will include routine chest physiotherapy, oxygen assessments, facilitating early discharge from hospital and promotion of self management. The post holder will work in collaboration with other services across the Trust and other stakeholders in order to make a positive impact on the health and well being of patients with chronic respiratory disease. They will also act as a resource for patients and other health professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is anticipated that the successful candidate will have an interest in respiratory and the community. Training and support will be available for candidates with the potential to develop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kristy Jenkins&lt;/strong&gt; - Community Respiratory Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kristy.jenkins@cpft.nhs.uk - 07790571689&lt;/p&gt;
